summary: Researchers at the McGill University, supported by funding from the National Institutes of Health (NIH), have created what is being called the smallest bioprinter reported to date—just 2.7 mm wide—that can accurately deliver hydrogels to vocal cords during surgery, helping prevent post-operative stiffness and improve patients’ ability to speak. title_en: Miniature Bioprinter Aims to Improve Vocal Cord Healing, Developed by McGill Researchers

The bioprinter is designed to deliver hydrogels to vocal cords during surgery.

The project received funding from the National Institutes of Health (NIH) and was published in the journal Cell.

Tato inovace má za cíl zabránit pooperační ztuhlosti a zlepšit schopnost pacientů mluvit.
Projekt byl financován Národními instituty zdraví (NIH) a publikován v časopise Cell.
